# UI Guidelines

## Theme System
- Use OKLCH color space for enhanced vibrancy
- Implement complete dark/light mode using next-themes
- Configure CSS variables for theme tokens
- Support system preference detection

## Component Usage
### ShadCN UI Components
✅ Use pre-built components for consistency:
- Dialog, Sheet, Card for containers
- Form, Input, Select for data entry
- Navigation Menu, Tabs for navigation
- Popover, HoverCard for overlays
- Command for search interfaces

### Custom Components
- Keep components small and focused
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Add comprehensive JSDoc comments
- Include Storybook documentation

### Collapsible Components
- Default to collapsed state for large content areas
- Use ChevronDown icon with rotation transform for toggle
- Include ARIA labels for accessibility
- Provide smooth animation transitions between states
- When appropriate, add alternative button/text to expand content

## Styling Best Practices
✅ Use Tailwind v4.0 utilities:
- Use semantic classes (bg-background/text-foreground)
- Implement responsive design utilities
- Apply animation configurations
- Use custom radius and spacing values

❌ Avoid:
- Direct color values
- Inline styles
- Non-semantic class names
- Unmaintainable animations

## Interactive Canvas
- Use React-Konva for canvas operations
- Implement smooth animations
- Ensure responsive behavior
- Handle touch and mouse events
- Optimize rendering performance

## Accessibility
- Ensure WCAG 2.1 compliance
- Test with screen readers
- Support keyboard navigation
- Maintain proper contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML elements 